In my decades of working within the various roles that form Enterprise Architecture, the community of practice is usually isolated to those to want to be, or think they want to be an enterprise architect. A good Enterprise Architect has usually had a spiral career that has meant lots of technical and management roles and is (usually) able to fill a skill gap on any team.

What I have learned over those same decades is that Enterprise Architecture is a team sport. If the various architecture deliverables are stored as only EA assets to be created and updated by those who have been anointed with the enterprise architecture title, the enterprise architecture practice is doomed.

Enterprise Architecture can and should be done by anyone.